# Settlement

## Overview

The Settlement module is responsible for coordinating the transition from validated operational decisions to trustless on-chain settlement.

ProofSettle does not replace settlement infrastructure. Instead, it ensures that every settlement is based on transparent, explainable, and independently verifiable operational decisions.

Settlement occurs only after the Decision Engine, Rules Engine, and Validation module have successfully completed their responsibilities.

---

## Responsibilities

- Receive settlement authorization.
- Prepare settlement payloads.
- Coordinate settlement execution.
- Record settlement references.
- Confirm settlement completion.
- Trigger Trust Receipt generation.

---

## Settlement Workflow

Every settlement follows the same deterministic workflow.

```
Settlement Authorization

        │

        ▼

Prepare Settlement Payload

        │

        ▼

Submit for Settlement

        │

        ▼

Transaction Confirmation

        │

        ▼

Settlement Reference

        │

        ▼

Trust Receipt Generation
```

---

## Settlement Requirements

Settlement proceeds only when:

- Verified Sports Intelligence has been processed.
- Decision Intelligence has completed.
- Business Rules have been successfully evaluated.
- Decision Validation has passed.
- Decision Artifact has been generated.
- Cryptographic verification has completed.
- Settlement authorization has been approved.

---

## Current Settlement Layer

The current architecture targets:

- Solana

Future versions may support additional settlement infrastructure while maintaining the same transparent decision workflow.

---

## Output

Successful settlement produces:

- Settlement Confirmation
- Transaction Reference
- Settlement Metadata
- Trust Receipt Trigger

These outputs are forwarded to the Trust Receipt module.

---

## Design Principles

The Settlement module follows several principles.

- Deterministic execution.
- Immutable settlement references.
- Separation of decision and settlement.
- Transparent authorization.
- Reliable transaction confirmation.

Settlement should be the result of a transparent operational decision—not the beginning of trust.

---

## Position in the Architecture

```
Decision Engine

        │

        ▼

Rules Engine

        │

        ▼

Validation

        │

        ▼

Settlement

        │

        ▼

Trust Receipt
```

---

The Settlement module completes the operational decision lifecycle by recording the immutable outcome while preserving the transparency established throughout the preceding decision journey.
